      "writtenOn": "2018-01-09T16:34:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: Other apps running in Skolo, e.g. hotspare and powercycle-daemon, already have direct access to the service account JWT, not running as root. Is there any reason metadata_server needs to be more secure (or is it wrong for hotspare, etc. to have access to the JWT)? Or would it be fine and simpler to just provide this app with the JWT and generate tokens directly (i.e. get rid of get_oauth2_token app)?",
      "revId": "4e863933c9def34172ade3e044b51836e2c5de26",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c638cc27_0e6769c1",
        "filename": "metadata_server/go/metadata_server/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 24,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-09T18:21:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My understanding is that it\u0027s not safe to have the JWT sitting on a machine (which is accessible from any machine in the lab) and readable by any user.  I was not aware that we already had the JWT on the machine.  What do those other apps need it for?",
      "parentUuid": "677c14ca_a971c7d4",
      "revId": "4e863933c9def34172ade3e044b51836e2c5de26",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
