    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d5929371_562fe658",
        "filename": "metadata_server/go/metadata_server/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 24,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-09T18:53:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "file-backup (for example) needs  auth.SCOPE_READ_WRITE, sklog.CLOUD_LOGGING_WRITE_SCOPE to write to the backup bucket.  It might also need it for cloud logging?  I can\u0027t quite remember.\n\nTo clarify, this on jumphost and rpi-master, which is only reachable from swarming bots if they know the login password (and we can lock that down even further if we want)\n\nAlthough we should probably change rpi-backup and hotspare to make the credentials not globally readable",
      "parentUuid": "444f0af1_22c6fdc1",
      "revId": "4e863933c9def34172ade3e044b51836e2c5de26",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1020b26a_f370b894",
        "filename": "metadata_server/go/metadata_server/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 24,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-09T18:57:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do they actually need the JWT itself, or could they use a token?",
      "parentUuid": "d5929371_562fe658",
      "revId": "4e863933c9def34172ade3e044b51836e2c5de26",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "63938e74_1d426bc7",
        "filename": "metadata_server/go/metadata_server/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 24,
      "author": {
        "id": 5205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-10T16:28:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If our \u0027go/auth\u0027 package doesn\u0027t support using a straight access token we can always update it so that it does. Given that, I agree that if we can just store an access token in the metadata and use that for backup then we should be moving to that.",
      "parentUuid": "1020b26a_f370b894",
      "revId": "4e863933c9def34172ade3e044b51836e2c5de26",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e79af205_72d29ab7",
        "filename": "metadata_server/go/metadata_server/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 24,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-10T18:10:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just to confirm, the following is the plan, correct?\n1. Add the metadata server on jumphosts.\n2. Implement a TokenSource that queries the jumphost metadata server.\n3. Use the new TokenSource for apps that need service account in Skolo.",
      "parentUuid": "63938e74_1d426bc7",
      "revId": "4e863933c9def34172ade3e044b51836e2c5de26",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7387041a_f2e95fda",
        "filename": "metadata_server/go/metadata_server/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 24,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-10T18:41:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Seems reasonable to me.  My only concern is that we only want to serve tokens for a single service account on a given jumphost.  Otherwise we have to try to enforce that certain machines get a certain account but not access to others.  That combined with the fact that we want the service accounts used by bots to have zero permissions may require us to do something else if there are apps that need more permissions.",
      "parentUuid": "e79af205_72d29ab7",
      "revId": "4e863933c9def34172ade3e044b51836e2c5de26",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    }
  ]
